1. Primena novog zakona u oblasti poreske politike je izazvala kontroverze. (*zakona*) (The implementation of the new law in the field of tax policy has caused controversy.)
2. Zakonodavni *zakon* je donet kako bi se regulisala pravila ponašanja članova parlamenta. (Legislative law was passed to regulate the code of conduct for members of parliament.)
3. Advokat je upoznat sa zakonima koji regulišu pravna pitanja u vezi sa razvodom braka. (*zakonima*) (The lawyer is familiar with the laws that regulate legal issues related to divorce.)
4. Policija sprovodi zakon i red u gradu. (*zakon*) (The police enforce law and order in the city.)
5. Ministarstvo pravde je zaduženo za primenu zakona u sudskom sistemu. (*zakona*) (The Ministry of Justice is responsible for the implementation of the law in the judicial system.)
6. Građani se pozivaju da poštuju zakonske propise o zaštiti životne sredine. (*zakonske*) (Citizens are called upon to respect legal regulations on environmental protection.)
7. Sudija je doneo odluku u skladu sa zakonom o nasleđivanju imovine. (*zakonom*) (The judge made a decision in accordance with the law on inheritance of property.)
8. Zakon o zaštiti potrošača štiti prava potrošača i reguliše poslovne aktivnosti prodavaca. (*zakon*) (The Consumer Protection Act protects consumer rights and regulates the business activities of sellers.)
9. Predloženi zakonski amandman bi omogućio produženje roka za registraciju vozila. (*zakonski*) (The proposed legal amendment would allow for an extension of the vehicle registration deadline.)
10. Poslodavci moraju da poštuju zakonske propise o radnom vremenu zaposlenih. (*zakonske*) (Employers must comply with legal regulations on working hours for employees.)